---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import SiteHeader from "../components/SiteHeader.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import Prose from "../components/Prose.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Cookies — Breaks"
  description="This site uses no cookies. The app uses none either."
  canonicalPath="/cookies"
>
  <SiteHeader />
  <main>
    <Prose
      eyebrow="Cookies"
      title="None. Not a single one."
      updated="28 April 2026"
    >
      <p>
        This website does not set cookies. Not first-party, not third-party,
        not for analytics, not for sessions, not for anything. There's nothing
        to consent to, so no banner appears.
      </p>

      <h2>The longer answer</h2>
      <p>
        The site is a static page hosted on GitHub Pages. It loads HTML, CSS,
        a small SVG favicon, and self-hosted fonts. That's all. No JavaScript
        runs in your browser beyond a tiny inline structured-data script.
      </p>
      <p>
        Local storage, session storage, IndexedDB, service workers, and similar
        storage mechanisms are also not used.
      </p>

      <h2>What about the app?</h2>
      <p>
        The Breaks app doesn't use cookies either. It stores its own settings
        in macOS <code>UserDefaults</code> on your machine. Nothing crosses the
        network. See the <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, "")}/privacy/`}>privacy page</a> for the full detail.
      </p>

      <h2>External links</h2>
      <p>
        If you click through to GitHub, those pages may set their own cookies
        per
        <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-general-privacy-statement" rel="noopener" target="_blank">GitHub's privacy statement</a>.
        We don't control those.
      </p>
    </Prose>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
